      <hedline>
        <hl1>RECORD PROFITS FOR OIL GIANT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>High crude oil prices and cost savings push second-quarter operating profits at Royal Dutch/Shell to record high, almost doubling to $3.15 billion from $1.61 billion year ago (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>High crude oil prices and cost savings pushed second-quarter operating profits at Royal Dutch/Shell to a record high, almost doubling to $3.15 billion from $1.61 billion a year ago, the company said. Shell, the world's second-largest publicly traded oil company, says it is saving $3 billion a year under a cost-cutting program.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell</p>
      </block>
